def _get_grouper(
    obj,
    key=None,
    axis=0,
    level=None,
    sort=True,
    observed=False,
    mutated=False,
    validate=True,
):
    group_axis = obj._get_axis(axis)

    # Check if key is a list
    if isinstance(key, list):
        results = {}
        for k in key:
            # Perform group operation for each key in the list
            results[k] = Grouping(
                group_axis,
                obj[k],
                obj=obj,
                name=k,
                level=level,
                sort=sort,
                observed=observed
            )
        
        return results, [], obj

    # Perform the regular group operation for a single key
    grouper = Grouping(
        group_axis,
        obj[key],
        obj=obj,
        name=key,
        level=level,
        sort=sort,
        observed=observed,
    )
    return grouper, [], obj
